title: Netanyahu demands Abbas, PA condemn West Bank murder
text: Photo: Mary Altaffer, AP Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu signs the United Nations guest book during a meeting with U.N. Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon, Thursday, Oct. 1, 2015 at U.N. Headquarters. Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu signs the United Nations... NEW YORK (AP) — Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on Friday demanded that Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas and his government explicitly condemn the murder of an Israeli settler couple by suspected Palestinian gunmen in the West Bank.
